  <article class="documentation-article">
    <h1>Exercise - Top Slice Method Valuation</h1>
    <h2>Build a NOI Statement to complete a Top Slice method valuation</h2>
    <p>
      It is year-end, you’ve been tasked with building a NOI Statement that
      includes last year's actuals and the upcoming year. The property is a
      40,000 square foot office which has been offering small serviced offices
      which can rent at a premium. Because of the non-traditional leasing model,
      your firm uses the Top Slice method for NOI Statements and valuations.
    </p>
    <h3 class="font-medium text-lg pt-2 tracking-wide">Serviced Office</h3>
    <p>
      However, as a serviced office the property earned $2,650,000 last year and
      had expenses of $675,000. Last year there was $85,000 in Turnover Costs
      and Free Rent Concessions given. Next year is expected to be the same.
    </p>
    <p>
      Serviced office doesn’t collect any Additional Rent, but does earn $60,000
      per year in parking and $30,000 in virtual mailbox revenue, both of which
      are expected to grow at 2% next year. There are no Vacancy or Credit
      Losses expected next year (operationally, you factor them into revenue
      expectations).
    </p>
    <h3 class="font-medium text-lg pt-2 tracking-wide">Theoretical Traditionally Leased Office</h3>
    <p>
      If the property was leased traditionally, the current annual Market Base
      Rent for the property would have earned $40 per square foot and the
      Operating Expenses would have been $400,000 per year. Similar office
      properties have Absorption, Turnover Vacancy & Other Concessions equal to
      $0.75 per square foot per year which is expected to grow at 2% per year.
    </p>
    <p>
      Traditional offices would typically recover 100% of the Operating Expenses
      and would also earn $60,000 in parking revenue per year.
    </p>
    <p>
      Similarly, office properties leased traditionally in this market suffer a
      Vacancy Loss of 3% and a Credit Loss of 2% of Potential Gross Income.
    </p>
    <h3 class="font-medium text-lg pt-2 tracking-wide">Growth</h3>
    <p>
      In the traditional leasing market, revenues and expenses are expected to
      be 2% higher next year. In the serviced office market, revenues and
      expenses are expected to be 4% higher next year.
    </p>
